    "recap_url": "https://www.upstatespartans.com/news/2026/3/20/behind-strong-bullpen-effort-baseball-rallies-for-two-in-the-ninth-downing-longwood-5-4-in-series-opener",
    "recap_headline": "University of South Carolina Upstate Athletics",
    "recap_text": "FARMVILLE, Va. \u2013\nFor the second time in as many games this week, USC Upstate baseball found a way to win, rallying back to with the go-ahead run in the ninth inning. The Spartans scratched a pair of runs in the final frame, fighting back to earn a 5-4 victory in Friday's series opener at Longwood.\nBridging the game to the offense in the ninth, Upstate's bullpen proved the stars for the second consecutive contest. Senior right-handed pitcher\nReece Hemmerling\n, redshirt freshman righty\nJacob Kirby\n, and sophomore left-hander\nMax Kaplan\ncombined to toss 3.0 scoreless frames while allowing two hits and four total baserunners.\nInheriting a pair of baserunners in the eighth\u2014the first inherited runners he's faced this season\u2014Kirby proceeded the strike out a pair and retire three straight runners en route to the win. Kaplan entered the game in the ninth, earning his second save of the season behind a clean frame.\nStarting on the mound, junior left-handed pitcher\nChris Torres\nturned in his first quality start of the campaign, working 6.0 innings while striking out six in his longest outing of the season.\nAt the plate, redshirt sophomore shortstop\nMaloy Heaghney\ncontinued his hot week at the plate, driving home two more RBI, upping his weekly total to eight. Fifth-year senior designated hitter\nJohnny Sweeney\nand redshirt sophomore centerfielder\nHenry Zenor\neach collected two hits.\nGame Information\nScore: USC Upstate 5; Longwood 4\nRecords: USC Upstate (12-11; 3-1 Big South); Longwood (15-7; 1-3 Big South)\nLocation: Buddy Bolding Stadium | Farmville, Va.\nHow It Happened\nB1: Getting on the board first, Longwood's Tre Keels launched a three-run home run to left-center.\nB2: Using a pair of sacrifices, the Lancers scratched another tally behind a sac fly from Brogan Jones.\nT5: Shooting a ball back through the box and against the shift,\nHenry Zenor\nplated the Spartans' first run of the night, scoring\nKenan Bowman\nfrom second.\nT6: Pulling Upstate closer,\nJohnny Sweeney\nlaced a solo shot into the tree in right, just missing the scoreboard.\nT7: Loading the bases behind the free pass, the Spartans used a free pass issued to\nMaloy Heaghney\nto scratch their third run.\nT9: Jumping on the first pitch he saw,\nMaloy Heaghney\ndropped a double into the left-center gap allowing pinch runners\nTrey Bentley\nand\nAlex Ritzer\nto score, the tying and go-ahead runs.\nNotable\nScoring a pair of runs in the ninth, Upstate fought back to earn its second straight ninth-inning comeback victory.\nIn the Spartans' two comeback wins, the bullpen has stranded seven straight runners as\nJacob Kirby\nstranded a pair Friday\u2014the first inherited runners he's faced this season.\nConnect with the Spartans\nFacebook.com/UpstateAthletics\nTwitter | @UpstateBSB | @UpstateSpartans\nInstagram | @UpstateBSB | @UpstateSpartans\nYouTube.com/UpstateSpartans\nINVEST IN CHAMPIONS\n- Join the Upstate Athletic Fund (UAF) and enjoy enhanced benefits for your support of all USC Upstate programs! Make your gift today,\nclick here\n!",
